	dprr:hasNoteText "Tr. pl. designatus in 100, for 99. See Val. Max. 3.2.18, and above, on L. Appuleius Saturninus (29); Wiseman, ,NM 229, no. 163.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3673> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3673" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "tr. pl. des. for 99. The two Tribunes were killed on their first day of office, December 10, 100 B.C. (App. BC 1.32-33; cf. Cic. Rab. Perd. 20; Val. Max. 3.2.18; Dio 37.26; and on Saturninus, Inscr. Ital. 13.3.16 and 83-CIL 12.1, p. 195; see 102, Censors; and 100, Consuls, and Tribunes of the Plebs)." .
